It seems to me that you do not have `mvn` installation.

&gt; but it does not recognize mvn command

Usually, after `mvn` installation you would have 

 - `~/.m2/settings.xml` (user specific profiles) or/and
 - `/usr/share/maven/conf/settings.xml` (On linux) 
 - `/opt/homebrew/Cellar/maven/3.8.7/libexec/conf/settings.xml` (On mac OS)

where you can define repositories from where you want to pull those packages. You can provide repositories in your `pom` as well. So for example, entry in the `settings.xml` would look like

```xml
...
&lt;profiles&gt;
 &lt;profile&gt;
      &lt;id&gt;maven&lt;/id&gt;
      &lt;repositories&gt;
        &lt;repository&gt;
          &lt;id&gt;mavevn_central&lt;/id&gt;
          &lt;name&gt;Default Repository&lt;/name&gt;
          &lt;layout&gt;default&lt;/layout&gt;
          &lt;url&gt;https://repo1.maven.org/maven2&lt;/url&gt;
          &lt;snapshots&gt;
            &lt;enabled&gt;false&lt;/enabled&gt;
          &lt;/snapshots&gt;
        &lt;/repository&gt;
      &lt;/repositories&gt;
    &lt;/profile&gt;
&lt;\profiles&gt;
...

```

Or in `pom.xml`
```xml
	&lt;repositories&gt;
		&lt;repository&gt;
			&lt;id&gt;mavevn_central&lt;/id&gt;
			&lt;name&gt;Default Repository&lt;/name&gt;
			&lt;layout&gt;default&lt;/layout&gt;
			&lt;url&gt;https://repo1.maven.org/maven2&lt;/url&gt;
			&lt;snapshots&gt;
				&lt;enabled&gt;false&lt;/enabled&gt;
			&lt;/snapshots&gt;
		&lt;/repository&gt;
	&lt;/repositories&gt;
```

When you will have this configuration, then in Intellij it is just:

 1. Go to pom.xml
 2. cmd + n --&gt; to invoke `generate`
 3. Choose `add dependency`
 4. Search for dependency and select
 5. Load maven changes

Default maven repository will be added after installation of `maven`. 

More at [Apache Maven][1]


  [1]: https://maven.apache.org/settings.html

