endInstant = 2023-11-30T18:30:00Z
start = 1698777000000
end = 1701369000000
```

To work with pairs of moments, I suggest adding the [*ThreeTen-Extra*][5] library to your project. That library includes the [`Interval`][6] class, to represent a span of time as a pair of `Instant` objects. That class offers several handy methods such as `contains`, `abuts`, and `intersection`. And that class parses/generates text in standard ISO 8601 format with two moments separate by a slash.

